{
  "stem": "22972.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I saw these makeshift Jewish schools, where kids were sitting on the floor, where they were sitting in circles, where there was no blackboard, there was no gym, there was no-- I-- I-- I was horrified.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And then, probably one of the last appointments of the day, we pulled up in front of this incredible villa, and I took one look at it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And we walked around it because we were a little early, because we had left the last appointment in horror early-- we didn't even ask for a tour of this makeshift thing.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "My father had already decided he was going to get tutors and have me tutored at home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we drove up in front of this villa im [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Roseneck, ?] and I looked at this thing and I saw that in back there was a full athletic field.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I literally-- I saw the French doors, going tall, French, glass doors-- and I literally thought I'd died and gone to heaven.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we had our appointment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And I took one look at the principal of the school, Frau Doctor Goldschmidt, and I had a crush on her, as did every single one of the 300 or so kids that went to her school.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We all adored this woman.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "She was the most extraordinary educator that the world ever created.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And I would like to talk about the Goldschmidt Schule in detail, if I may.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "She had, as every other Jewish teacher, been fired in 1935 when the Nuremberg Laws came out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But before 1935, she had taken a sabbatical in England-- probably in '33, '32, '33-- and she had taught in England.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
